Detailed Description

SelectionDAG class - This is used to represent a portion of an LLVM function in a low-level Data Dependence DAG representation suitable for instruction selection. This DAG is constructed as the first step of instruction selection in order to allow implementation of machine specific optimizations and code simplifications.

The representation used by the SelectionDAG is a target-independent representation, which has some similarities to the GCC RTL representation, but is significantly more simple, powerful, and is a graph form instead of a linear form.

Definition at line 6118 of file SelectionDAG.cpp.

6118  {
6119 
6120  unsigned DAGSize = 0;
6121 
6122  // SortedPos tracks the progress of the algorithm. Nodes before it are
6123  // sorted, nodes after it are unsorted. When the algorithm completes
6124  // it is at the end of the list.
6125  allnodes_iterator SortedPos = allnodes_begin();
6126 
6127  // Visit all the nodes. Move nodes with no operands to the front of
6128  // the list immediately. Annotate nodes that do have operands with their
6129  // operand count. Before we do this, the Node Id fields of the nodes
6130  // may contain arbitrary values. After, the Node Id fields for nodes
6131  // before SortedPos will contain the topological sort index, and the
6132  // Node Id fields for nodes At SortedPos and after will contain the
6133  // count of outstanding operands.
6134  for (allnodes_iterator I = allnodes_begin(),E = allnodes_end(); I != E; ) {
6135  SDNode *N = I++;
6136  checkForCycles(N, this);
6137  unsigned Degree = N->getNumOperands();
6138  if (Degree == 0) {
6139  // A node with no uses, add it to the result array immediately.
6140  N->setNodeId(DAGSize++);
6141  allnodes_iterator Q = N;
6142  if (Q != SortedPos)
6143  SortedPos = AllNodes.insert(SortedPos, AllNodes.remove(Q));
6144  assert(SortedPos != AllNodes.end() && "Overran node list");
6145  ++SortedPos;
6146  } else {
6147  // Temporarily use the Node Id as scratch space for the degree count.
6148  N->setNodeId(Degree);
6149  }
6150  }
6151 
6152  // Visit all the nodes. As we iterate, move nodes into sorted order,
6153  // such that by the time the end is reached all nodes will be sorted.
6154  for (allnodes_iterator I = allnodes_begin(),E = allnodes_end(); I != E; ++I) {
6155  SDNode *N = I;
6156  checkForCycles(N, this);
6157  // N is in sorted position, so all its uses have one less operand
6158  // that needs to be sorted.
6159  for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = N->use_begin(), UE = N->use_end();
6160  UI != UE; ++UI) {
6161  SDNode *P = *UI;
6162  unsigned Degree = P->getNodeId();
6163  assert(Degree != 0 && "Invalid node degree");
6164  --Degree;
6165  if (Degree == 0) {
6166  // All of P's operands are sorted, so P may sorted now.
6167  P->setNodeId(DAGSize++);
6168  if (P != SortedPos)
6169  SortedPos = AllNodes.insert(SortedPos, AllNodes.remove(P));
6170  assert(SortedPos != AllNodes.end() && "Overran node list");
6171  ++SortedPos;
6172  } else {
6173  // Update P's outstanding operand count.
6174  P->setNodeId(Degree);
6175  }
6176  }
6177  if (I == SortedPos) {
6178 #ifndef NDEBUG
6179  SDNode *S = ++I;
6180  dbgs() << "Overran sorted position:\n";
6181  S->dumprFull(this); dbgs() << "\n";
6182  dbgs() << "Checking if this is due to cycles\n";
6183  checkForCycles(this, true);
6184 #endif
6185  llvm_unreachable(nullptr);
6186  }

6190  "Topological sort incomplete!");

6192  "First node in topological sort is not the entry token!");

void SelectionDAG::computeKnownBits ( SDValue  Op,
APInt &  KnownZero,
APInt &  KnownOne,
unsigned  Depth = 0 
) const

Determine which bits of Op are known to be either zero or one and return them in the KnownZero/KnownOne bitsets. Targets can implement the computeKnownBitsForTargetNode method in the TargetLowering class to allow target nodes to be understood.

Determine which bits of Op are known to be either zero or one and return them in the KnownZero/KnownOne bitsets.

Definition at line 1943 of file SelectionDAG.cpp.

1944  {
1945  const TargetLowering *TLI = TM.getTargetLowering();
1946  unsigned BitWidth = Op.getValueType().getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
1947 
1948  KnownZero = KnownOne = APInt(BitWidth, 0); // Don't know anything.
1949  if (Depth == 6)
1950  return; // Limit search depth.
1951 
1952  APInt KnownZero2, KnownOne2;
1953 
1954  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
1955  case ISD::Constant:
1956  // We know all of the bits for a constant!
1957  KnownOne = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)->getAPIntValue();
1958  KnownZero = ~KnownOne;
1959  break;
1960  case ISD::AND:
1961  // If either the LHS or the RHS are Zero, the result is zero.
1962  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
1963  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
1964 
1965  // Output known-1 bits are only known if set in both the LHS & RHS.
1966  KnownOne &= KnownOne2;
1967  // Output known-0 are known to be clear if zero in either the LHS | RHS.
1968  KnownZero |= KnownZero2;
1969  break;
1970  case ISD::OR:
1971  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
1972  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
1973 
1974  // Output known-0 bits are only known if clear in both the LHS & RHS.
1975  KnownZero &= KnownZero2;
1976  // Output known-1 are known to be set if set in either the LHS | RHS.
1977  KnownOne |= KnownOne2;
1978  break;
1979  case ISD::XOR: {
1980  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
1981  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
1982 
1983  // Output known-0 bits are known if clear or set in both the LHS & RHS.
1984  APInt KnownZeroOut = (KnownZero & KnownZero2) | (KnownOne & KnownOne2);
1985  // Output known-1 are known to be set if set in only one of the LHS, RHS.
1986  KnownOne = (KnownZero & KnownOne2) | (KnownOne & KnownZero2);
1987  KnownZero = KnownZeroOut;
1988  break;
1989  }
1990  case ISD::MUL: {
1991  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
1992  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
1993 
1994  // If low bits are zero in either operand, output low known-0 bits.
1995  // Also compute a conserative estimate for high known-0 bits.
1996  // More trickiness is possible, but this is sufficient for the
1997  // interesting case of alignment computation.
1998  KnownOne.clearAllBits();
1999  unsigned TrailZ = KnownZero.countTrailingOnes() +
2000  KnownZero2.countTrailingOnes();
2001  unsigned LeadZ = std::max(KnownZero.countLeadingOnes() +
2002  KnownZero2.countLeadingOnes(),
2003  BitWidth) - BitWidth;
2004 
2005  TrailZ = std::min(TrailZ, BitWidth);
2006  LeadZ = std::min(LeadZ, BitWidth);
2007  KnownZero = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, TrailZ) |
2008  APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, LeadZ);
2009  break;
2010  }
2011  case ISD::UDIV: {
2012  // For the purposes of computing leading zeros we can conservatively
2013  // treat a udiv as a logical right shift by the power of 2 known to
2014  // be less than the denominator.
2015  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2016  unsigned LeadZ = KnownZero2.countLeadingOnes();
2017 
2018  KnownOne2.clearAllBits();
2019  KnownZero2.clearAllBits();
2020  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2021  unsigned RHSUnknownLeadingOnes = KnownOne2.countLeadingZeros();
2022  if (RHSUnknownLeadingOnes != BitWidth)
2023  LeadZ = std::min(BitWidth,
2024  LeadZ + BitWidth - RHSUnknownLeadingOnes - 1);
2025 
2026  KnownZero = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, LeadZ);
2027  break;
2028  }
2029  case ISD::SELECT:
2030  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2031  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2032 
2033  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
2034  KnownOne &= KnownOne2;
2035  KnownZero &= KnownZero2;
2036  break;
2037  case ISD::SELECT_CC:
2038  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(3), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2039  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(2), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2040 
2041  // Only known if known in both the LHS and RHS.
2042  KnownOne &= KnownOne2;
2043  KnownZero &= KnownZero2;
2044  break;
2045  case ISD::SADDO:
2046  case ISD::UADDO:
2047  case ISD::SSUBO:
2048  case ISD::USUBO:
2049  case ISD::SMULO:
2050  case ISD::UMULO:
2051  if (Op.getResNo() != 1)
2052  break;
2053  // The boolean result conforms to getBooleanContents.
2054  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
2055  // We know that we have an integer-based boolean since these operations
2056  // are only available for integer.
2057  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getValueType().isVector(), false) ==
2058  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
2059  BitWidth > 1)
2060  KnownZero |= APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - 1);
2061  break;
2062  case ISD::SETCC:
2063  // If we know the result of a setcc has the top bits zero, use this info.
2064  if (TLI->getBooleanContents(Op.getOperand(0).getValueType()) ==
2065  TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent &&
2066  BitWidth > 1)
2067  KnownZero |= APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - 1);
2068  break;
2069  case ISD::SHL:
2070  // (shl X, C1) & C2 == 0 iff (X & C2 >>u C1) == 0
2071  if (ConstantSDNode *SA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
2072  unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
2073 
2074  // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
2075  if (ShAmt >= BitWidth)
2076  break;
2077 
2078  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2079  KnownZero <<= ShAmt;
2080  KnownOne <<= ShAmt;
2081  // low bits known zero.
2082  KnownZero |= APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, ShAmt);
2083  }
2084  break;
2085  case ISD::SRL:
2086  // (ushr X, C1) & C2 == 0 iff (-1 >> C1) & C2 == 0
2087  if (ConstantSDNode *SA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
2088  unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
2089 
2090  // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
2091  if (ShAmt >= BitWidth)
2092  break;
2093 
2094  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2095  KnownZero = KnownZero.lshr(ShAmt);
2096  KnownOne = KnownOne.lshr(ShAmt);
2097 
2098  APInt HighBits = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, ShAmt);
2099  KnownZero |= HighBits; // High bits known zero.
2100  }
2101  break;
2102  case ISD::SRA:
2103  if (ConstantSDNode *SA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
2104  unsigned ShAmt = SA->getZExtValue();
2105 
2106  // If the shift count is an invalid immediate, don't do anything.
2107  if (ShAmt >= BitWidth)
2108  break;
2109 
2110  // If any of the demanded bits are produced by the sign extension, we also
2111  // demand the input sign bit.
2112  APInt HighBits = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, ShAmt);
2113 
2114  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2115  KnownZero = KnownZero.lshr(ShAmt);
2116  KnownOne = KnownOne.lshr(ShAmt);
2117 
2118  // Handle the sign bits.
2119  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignBit(BitWidth);
2120  SignBit = SignBit.lshr(ShAmt); // Adjust to where it is now in the mask.
2121 
2122  if (KnownZero.intersects(SignBit)) {
2123  KnownZero |= HighBits; // New bits are known zero.
2124  } else if (KnownOne.intersects(SignBit)) {
2125  KnownOne |= HighBits; // New bits are known one.
2126  }
2127  }
2128  break;
2129  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
2130  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
2131  unsigned EBits = EVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2132 
2133  // Sign extension. Compute the demanded bits in the result that are not
2134  // present in the input.
2135  APInt NewBits = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - EBits);
2136 
2137  APInt InSignBit = APInt::getSignBit(EBits);
2138  APInt InputDemandedBits = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, EBits);
2139 
2140  // If the sign extended bits are demanded, we know that the sign
2141  // bit is demanded.
2142  InSignBit = InSignBit.zext(BitWidth);
2143  if (NewBits.getBoolValue())
2144  InputDemandedBits |= InSignBit;
2145 
2146  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2147  KnownOne &= InputDemandedBits;
2148  KnownZero &= InputDemandedBits;
2149 
2150  // If the sign bit of the input is known set or clear, then we know the
2151  // top bits of the result.
2152  if (KnownZero.intersects(InSignBit)) { // Input sign bit known clear
2153  KnownZero |= NewBits;
2154  KnownOne &= ~NewBits;
2155  } else if (KnownOne.intersects(InSignBit)) { // Input sign bit known set
2156  KnownOne |= NewBits;
2157  KnownZero &= ~NewBits;
2158  } else { // Input sign bit unknown
2159  KnownZero &= ~NewBits;
2160  KnownOne &= ~NewBits;
2161  }
2162  break;
2163  }
2164  case ISD::CTTZ:
2165  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2166  case ISD::CTLZ:
2167  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2168  case ISD::CTPOP: {
2169  unsigned LowBits = Log2_32(BitWidth)+1;
2170  KnownZero = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - LowBits);
2171  KnownOne.clearAllBits();
2172  break;
2173  }
2174  case ISD::LOAD: {
2175  LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
2176  // If this is a ZEXTLoad and we are looking at the loaded value.
2177  if (ISD::isZEXTLoad(Op.getNode()) && Op.getResNo() == 0) {
2178  EVT VT = LD->getMemoryVT();
2179  unsigned MemBits = VT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2180  KnownZero |= APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - MemBits);
2181  } else if (const MDNode *Ranges = LD->getRanges()) {
2182  computeKnownBitsFromRangeMetadata(*Ranges, KnownZero);
2183  }
2184  break;
2185  }
2186  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: {
2187  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2188  unsigned InBits = InVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2189  APInt NewBits = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - InBits);
2190  KnownZero = KnownZero.trunc(InBits);
2191  KnownOne = KnownOne.trunc(InBits);
2192  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2193  KnownZero = KnownZero.zext(BitWidth);
2194  KnownOne = KnownOne.zext(BitWidth);
2195  KnownZero |= NewBits;
2196  break;
2197  }
2198  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: {
2199  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2200  unsigned InBits = InVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2201  APInt NewBits = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - InBits);
2202 
2203  KnownZero = KnownZero.trunc(InBits);
2204  KnownOne = KnownOne.trunc(InBits);
2205  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2206 
2207  // Note if the sign bit is known to be zero or one.
2208  bool SignBitKnownZero = KnownZero.isNegative();
2209  bool SignBitKnownOne = KnownOne.isNegative();
2210 
2211  KnownZero = KnownZero.zext(BitWidth);
2212  KnownOne = KnownOne.zext(BitWidth);
2213 
2214  // If the sign bit is known zero or one, the top bits match.
2215  if (SignBitKnownZero)
2216  KnownZero |= NewBits;
2217  else if (SignBitKnownOne)
2218  KnownOne |= NewBits;
2219  break;
2220  }
2221  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: {
2222  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2223  unsigned InBits = InVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2224  KnownZero = KnownZero.trunc(InBits);
2225  KnownOne = KnownOne.trunc(InBits);
2226  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2227  KnownZero = KnownZero.zext(BitWidth);
2228  KnownOne = KnownOne.zext(BitWidth);
2229  break;
2230  }
2231  case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
2232  EVT InVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
2233  unsigned InBits = InVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
2234  KnownZero = KnownZero.zext(InBits);
2235  KnownOne = KnownOne.zext(InBits);
2236  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2237  KnownZero = KnownZero.trunc(BitWidth);
2238  KnownOne = KnownOne.trunc(BitWidth);
2239  break;
2240  }
2241  case ISD::AssertZext: {
2242  EVT VT = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
2243  APInt InMask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, VT.getSizeInBits());
2244  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2245  KnownZero |= (~InMask);
2246  KnownOne &= (~KnownZero);
2247  break;
2248  }
2249  case ISD::FGETSIGN:
2250  // All bits are zero except the low bit.
2251  KnownZero = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - 1);
2252  break;
2253 
2254  case ISD::SUB: {
2255  if (ConstantSDNode *CLHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))) {
2256  // We know that the top bits of C-X are clear if X contains less bits
2257  // than C (i.e. no wrap-around can happen). For example, 20-X is
2258  // positive if we can prove that X is >= 0 and < 16.
2259  if (CLHS->getAPIntValue().isNonNegative()) {
2260  unsigned NLZ = (CLHS->getAPIntValue()+1).countLeadingZeros();
2261  // NLZ can't be BitWidth with no sign bit
2262  APInt MaskV = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, NLZ+1);
2263  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2264 
2265  // If all of the MaskV bits are known to be zero, then we know the
2266  // output top bits are zero, because we now know that the output is
2267  // from [0-C].
2268  if ((KnownZero2 & MaskV) == MaskV) {
2269  unsigned NLZ2 = CLHS->getAPIntValue().countLeadingZeros();
2270  // Top bits known zero.
2271  KnownZero = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, NLZ2);
2272  }
2273  }
2274  }
2275  }
2276  // fall through
2277  case ISD::ADD:
2278  case ISD::ADDE: {
2279  // Output known-0 bits are known if clear or set in both the low clear bits
2280  // common to both LHS & RHS. For example, 8+(X<<3) is known to have the
2281  // low 3 bits clear.
2282  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2283  unsigned KnownZeroOut = KnownZero2.countTrailingOnes();
2284 
2285  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2286  KnownZeroOut = std::min(KnownZeroOut,
2287  KnownZero2.countTrailingOnes());
2288 
2289  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
2290  KnownZero |= APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, KnownZeroOut);
2291  break;
2292  }
2293 
2294  // With ADDE, a carry bit may be added in, so we can only use this
2295  // information if we know (at least) that the low two bits are clear. We
2296  // then return to the caller that the low bit is unknown but that other bits
2297  // are known zero.
2298  if (KnownZeroOut >= 2) // ADDE
2299  KnownZero |= APInt::getBitsSet(BitWidth, 1, KnownZeroOut);
2300  break;
2301  }
2302  case ISD::SREM:
2303  if (ConstantSDNode *Rem = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
2304  const APInt &RA = Rem->getAPIntValue().abs();
2305  if (RA.isPowerOf2()) {
2306  APInt LowBits = RA - 1;
2307  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2,KnownOne2,Depth+1);
2308 
2309  // The low bits of the first operand are unchanged by the srem.
2310  KnownZero = KnownZero2 & LowBits;
2311  KnownOne = KnownOne2 & LowBits;
2312 
2313  // If the first operand is non-negative or has all low bits zero, then
2314  // the upper bits are all zero.
2315  if (KnownZero2[BitWidth-1] || ((KnownZero2 & LowBits) == LowBits))
2316  KnownZero |= ~LowBits;
2317 
2318  // If the first operand is negative and not all low bits are zero, then
2319  // the upper bits are all one.
2320  if (KnownOne2[BitWidth-1] && ((KnownOne2 & LowBits) != 0))
2321  KnownOne |= ~LowBits;
2322  assert((KnownZero & KnownOne) == 0&&"Bits known to be one AND zero?");
2323  }
2324  }
2325  break;
2326  case ISD::UREM: {
2327  if (ConstantSDNode *Rem = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
2328  const APInt &RA = Rem->getAPIntValue();
2329  if (RA.isPowerOf2()) {
2330  APInt LowBits = (RA - 1);
2331  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth + 1);
2332 
2333  // The upper bits are all zero, the lower ones are unchanged.
2334  KnownZero = KnownZero2 | ~LowBits;
2335  KnownOne = KnownOne2 & LowBits;
2336  break;
2337  }
2338  }
2339 
2340  // Since the result is less than or equal to either operand, any leading
2341  // zero bits in either operand must also exist in the result.
2342  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(0), KnownZero, KnownOne, Depth+1);
2343  computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(1), KnownZero2, KnownOne2, Depth+1);
2344 
2345  uint32_t Leaders = std::max(KnownZero.countLeadingOnes(),
2346  KnownZero2.countLeadingOnes());
2347  KnownOne.clearAllBits();
2348  KnownZero = APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, Leaders);
2349  break;
2350  }
2351  case ISD::FrameIndex:
2352  case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
2353  if (unsigned Align = InferPtrAlignment(Op)) {
2354  // The low bits are known zero if the pointer is aligned.
2355  KnownZero = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, Log2_32(Align));
2356  break;
2357  }
2358  break;
2359 
2360  default:
2361  if (Op.getOpcode() < ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END)
2362  break;
2363  // Fallthrough
2364  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
2365  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
2366  case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
2367  // Allow the target to implement this method for its nodes.
2368  TLI->computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(Op, KnownZero, KnownOne, *this, Depth);
2369  break;
2370  }
2371 
2372  assert((KnownZero & KnownOne) == 0 && "Bits known to be one AND zero?");
2373 }

unsigned SelectionDAG::ComputeNumSignBits ( SDValue  Op,
unsigned  Depth = 0 
) const

ComputeNumSignBits - Return the number of times the sign bit of the register is replicated into the other bits. We know that at least 1 bit is always equal to the sign bit (itself), but other cases can give us information. For example, immediately after an "SRA X, 2", we know that the top 3 bits are all equal to each other, so we return 3. Targets can implement the ComputeNumSignBitsForTarget method in the TargetLowering class to allow target nodes to be understood.

ComputeNumSignBits - Return the number of times the sign bit of the register is replicated into the other bits. We know that at least 1 bit is always equal to the sign bit (itself), but other cases can give us information. For example, immediately after an "SRA X, 2", we know that the top 3 bits are all equal to each other, so we return 3.

1844  const APInt &C1 = N1C->getAPIntValue();
1845 
1846  switch (Cond) {
1847  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer setcc!");
1848  case ISD::SETEQ: return getConstant(C1 == C2, VT);
1849  case ISD::SETNE: return getConstant(C1 != C2, VT);
1850  case ISD::SETULT: return getConstant(C1.ult(C2), VT);
1851  case ISD::SETUGT: return getConstant(C1.ugt(C2), VT);
1852  case ISD::SETULE: return getConstant(C1.ule(C2), VT);
1853  case ISD::SETUGE: return getConstant(C1.uge(C2), VT);
1854  case ISD::SETLT: return getConstant(C1.slt(C2), VT);
1855  case ISD::SETGT: return getConstant(C1.sgt(C2), VT);
1856  case ISD::SETLE: return getConstant(C1.sle(C2), VT);
1857  case ISD::SETGE: return getConstant(C1.sge(C2), VT);
1858  }
1859  }
1860  }
1861  if (ConstantFPSDNode *N1C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1.getNode())) {
1862  if (ConstantFPSDNode *N2C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2.getNode())) {
1863  APFloat::cmpResult R = N1C->getValueAPF().compare(N2C->getValueAPF());
1864  switch (Cond) {
1865  default: break;
1866  case ISD::SETEQ: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1867  return getUNDEF(VT);
1868  // fall through
1869  case ISD::SETOEQ: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpEqual, VT);
1870  case ISD::SETNE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1871  return getUNDEF(VT);
1872  // fall through
1873  case ISD::SETONE: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
1874  R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, VT);
1875  case ISD::SETLT: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1876  return getUNDEF(VT);
1877  // fall through
1878  case ISD::SETOLT: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, VT);
1879  case ISD::SETGT: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1880  return getUNDEF(VT);
1881  // fall through
1882  case ISD::SETOGT: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan, VT);
1883  case ISD::SETLE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1884  return getUNDEF(VT);
1885  // fall through
1886  case ISD::SETOLE: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpLessThan ||
1887  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, VT);
1888  case ISD::SETGE: if (R==APFloat::cmpUnordered)
1889  return getUNDEF(VT);
1890  // fall through
1891  case ISD::SETOGE: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
1892  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, VT);
1893  case ISD::SETO: return getConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpUnordered, VT);
1894  case ISD::SETUO: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered, VT);
1895  case ISD::SETUEQ: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered ||
1896  R==APFloat::cmpEqual, VT);
1897  case ISD::SETUNE: return getConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpEqual, VT);
1898  case ISD::SETULT: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpUnordered ||
1899  R==APFloat::cmpLessThan, VT);
1900  case ISD::SETUGT: return getConstant(R==APFloat::cmpGreaterThan ||
1901  R==APFloat::cmpUnordered, VT);
1902  case ISD::SETULE: return getConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpGreaterThan, VT);
1903  case ISD::SETUGE: return getConstant(R!=APFloat::cmpLessThan, VT);
1904  }
1905  } else {
1906  // Ensure that the constant occurs on the RHS.
1907  ISD::CondCode SwappedCond = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(Cond);
1908  MVT CompVT = N1.getValueType().getSimpleVT();
1909  if (!TM.getTargetLowering()->isCondCodeLegal(SwappedCond, CompVT))
1910  return SDValue();
1911 
1912  return getSetCC(dl, VT, N2, N1, SwappedCond);
1913  }
1914  }
1915 
1916  // Could not fold it.
1917  return SDValue();
1918 }

getAtomicCmpSwap - Gets a node for an atomic cmpxchg op. There are two valid Opcodes. ISD::ATOMIC_CMO_SWAP produces a the value loaded and a chain result. ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS produces the value loaded, a success flag (initially i1), and a chain.

1109  const ConstantInt *Elt = &Val;

1111  const TargetLowering *TLI = TM.getTargetLowering();
1112 
1113  // In some cases the vector type is legal but the element type is illegal and
1114  // needs to be promoted, for example v8i8 on ARM. In this case, promote the
1115  // inserted value (the type does not need to match the vector element type).
1116  // Any extra bits introduced will be truncated away.
1117  if (VT.isVector() && TLI->getTypeAction(*getContext(), EltVT) ==
1118  TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
1119  EltVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), EltVT);
1120  APInt NewVal = Elt->getValue().zext(EltVT.getSizeInBits());
1121  Elt = ConstantInt::get(*getContext(), NewVal);
1122  }
1123  // In other cases the element type is illegal and needs to be expanded, for
1124  // example v2i64 on MIPS32. In this case, find the nearest legal type, split
1125  // the value into n parts and use a vector type with n-times the elements.
1126  // Then bitcast to the type requested.
1127  // Legalizing constants too early makes the DAGCombiner's job harder so we
1128  // only legalize if the DAG tells us we must produce legal types.
1129  else if (NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes && VT.isVector() &&
1130  TLI->getTypeAction(*getContext(), EltVT) ==
1131  TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger) {
1132  APInt NewVal = Elt->getValue();
1133  EVT ViaEltVT = TLI->getTypeToTransformTo(*getContext(), EltVT);
1134  unsigned ViaEltSizeInBits = ViaEltVT.getSizeInBits();
1135  unsigned ViaVecNumElts = VT.getSizeInBits() / ViaEltSizeInBits;
1136  EVT ViaVecVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*getContext(), ViaEltVT, ViaVecNumElts);
1137 
1138  // Check the temporary vector is the correct size. If this fails then
1139  // getTypeToTransformTo() probably returned a type whose size (in bits)
1140  // isn't a power-of-2 factor of the requested type size.
1141  assert(ViaVecVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits());
1142 
1143  SmallVector<SDValue, 2> EltParts;
1144  for (unsigned i = 0; i < ViaVecNumElts / VT.getVectorNumElements(); ++i) {
1145  EltParts.push_back(getConstant(NewVal.lshr(i * ViaEltSizeInBits)
1146  .trunc(ViaEltSizeInBits),
1147  ViaEltVT, isT, isO));
1148  }
1149 
1150  // EltParts is currently in little endian order. If we actually want
1151  // big-endian order then reverse it now.
1152  if (TLI->isBigEndian())
1153  std::reverse(EltParts.begin(), EltParts.end());
1154 
1155  // The elements must be reversed when the element order is different
1156  // to the endianness of the elements (because the BITCAST is itself a
1157  // vector shuffle in this situation). However, we do not need any code to
1158  // perform this reversal because getConstant() is producing a vector
1159  // splat.
1160  // This situation occurs in MIPS MSA.
1161 
1162  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
1163  for (unsigned i = 0; i < VT.getVectorNumElements(); ++i)
1164  Ops.insert(Ops.end(), EltParts.begin(), EltParts.end());
1165 
1166  SDValue Result = getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(), VT,
1167  getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SDLoc(), ViaVecVT,
1168  Ops));
1169  return Result;
1170  }
1171 
1172  assert(Elt->getBitWidth() == EltVT.getSizeInBits() &&
1173  "APInt size does not match type size!");
1174  unsigned Opc = isT ? ISD::TargetConstant : ISD::Constant;
1175  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
1176  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opc, getVTList(EltVT), None);
1177  ID.AddPointer(Elt);
1178  ID.AddBoolean(isO);
1179  void *IP = nullptr;
1180  SDNode *N = nullptr;
1181  if ((N = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, IP)))
1182  if (!VT.isVector())
1183  return SDValue(N, 0);
1184 
1185  if (!N) {
1186  N = new (NodeAllocator) ConstantSDNode(isT, isO, Elt, EltVT);
1187  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
1188  AllNodes.push_back(N);
1189  }
1190 
1191  SDValue Result(N, 0);
1192  if (VT.isVector()) {
1193  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
1194  Ops.assign(VT.getVectorNumElements(), Result);
1195  Result = getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SDLoc(), VT, Ops);
1196  }
1197  return Result;
1198 }

getMachineNode - These are used for target selectors to create a new node with specified return type(s), MachineInstr opcode, and operands.

Note that getMachineNode returns the resultant node. If there is already a node of the specified opcode and operands, it returns that node instead of the current one.

4233  // Check to see if we should lower the memcpy to loads and stores first.
4234  // For cases within the target-specified limits, this is the best choice.
4235  ConstantSDNode *ConstantSize = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Size);

2687  {
2688  // Constant fold unary operations with an integer constant operand. Even
2689  // opaque constant will be folded, because the folding of unary operations
2690  // doesn't create new constants with different values. Nevertheless, the
2691  // opaque flag is preserved during folding to prevent future folding with
2692  // other constants.
2693  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Operand.getNode())) {
2694  const APInt &Val = C->getAPIntValue();
2695  switch (Opcode) {
2696  default: break;
2697  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2698  return getConstant(Val.sextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), VT,
2699  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
2700  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
2701  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2702  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
2703  return getConstant(Val.zextOrTrunc(VT.getSizeInBits()), VT,
2704  C->isTargetOpcode(), C->isOpaque());
2705  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
2706  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: {
2707  APFloat apf(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
2708  APInt::getNullValue(VT.getSizeInBits()));
2709  (void)apf.convertFromAPInt(Val,
2710  Opcode==ISD::SINT_TO_FP,
2711  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2712  return getConstantFP(apf, VT);
2713  }
2714  case ISD::BITCAST:
2715  if (VT == MVT::f32 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32)
2716  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEsingle, Val), VT);
2717  else if (VT == MVT::f64 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64)
2718  return getConstantFP(APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble, Val), VT);
2719  break;
2720  case ISD::BSWAP:
2721  return getConstant(Val.byteSwap(), VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
2722  C->isOpaque());
2723  case ISD::CTPOP:
2724  return getConstant(Val.countPopulation(), VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
2725  C->isOpaque());
2726  case ISD::CTLZ:
2727  case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2728  return getConstant(Val.countLeadingZeros(), VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
2729  C->isOpaque());
2730  case ISD::CTTZ:
2731  case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2732  return getConstant(Val.countTrailingZeros(), VT, C->isTargetOpcode(),
2733  C->isOpaque());
2734  }
2735  }
2736 
2737  // Constant fold unary operations with a floating point constant operand.
2738  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Operand.getNode())) {
2739  APFloat V = C->getValueAPF(); // make copy
2740  switch (Opcode) {
2741  case ISD::FNEG:
2742  V.changeSign();
2743  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2744  case ISD::FABS:
2745  V.clearSign();
2746  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2747  case ISD::FCEIL: {
2748  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardPositive);
2749  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
2750  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2751  break;
2752  }
2753  case ISD::FTRUNC: {
2754  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardZero);
2755  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
2756  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2757  break;
2758  }
2759  case ISD::FFLOOR: {
2760  APFloat::opStatus fs = V.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
2761  if (fs == APFloat::opOK || fs == APFloat::opInexact)
2762  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2763  break;
2764  }
2765  case ISD::FP_EXTEND: {
2766  bool ignored;
2767  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
2768  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
2769  (void)V.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
2770  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored);
2771  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
2772  }
2773  case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
2774  case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: {
2775  integerPart x[2];
2776  bool ignored;
2777  assert(integerPartWidth >= 64);
2778  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
2779  APFloat::opStatus s = V.convertToInteger(x, VT.getSizeInBits(),
2780  Opcode==ISD::FP_TO_SINT,
2781  APFloat::rmTowardZero, &ignored);
2782  if (s==APFloat::opInvalidOp) // inexact is OK, in fact usual
2783  break;
2784  APInt api(VT.getSizeInBits(), x);
2785  return getConstant(api, VT);
2786  }
2787  case ISD::BITCAST:
2788  if (VT == MVT::i32 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::f32)
2789  return getConstant((uint32_t)V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), VT);
2790  else if (VT == MVT::i64 && C->getValueType(0) == MVT::f64)
2791  return getConstant(V.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), VT);
2792  break;
2793  }
2794  }
2795 
2796  // Constant fold unary operations with a vector integer operand.
2797  if (BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Operand.getNode())) {
2798  if (BV->isConstant()) {
2799  switch (Opcode) {
2800  default:
2801  // FIXME: Entirely reasonable to perform folding of other unary
2802  // operations here as the need arises.
2803  break;
2804  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
2805  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: {
2806  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
2807  for (int i = 0, e = VT.getVectorNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
2808  SDValue OpN = BV->getOperand(i);
2809  // Let the above scalar folding handle the conversion of each
2810  // element.
2811  OpN = getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, DL, VT.getVectorElementType(),
2812  OpN);
2813  Ops.push_back(OpN);
2814  }
2815  return getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, DL, VT, Ops);
2816  }
2817  }
2818  }
2819  }
2820 
2821  unsigned OpOpcode = Operand.getNode()->getOpcode();
2822  switch (Opcode) {
2823  case ISD::TokenFactor:
2824  case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
2825  case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
2826  return Operand; // Factor, merge or concat of one node? No need.
2827  case ISD::FP_ROUND: llvm_unreachable("Invalid method to make FP_ROUND node");
2828  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
2829  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() &&
2830  Operand.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() && "Invalid FP cast!");
2831  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop conversion.
2832  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
2833  VT.getVectorNumElements() ==
2834  Operand.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2835  "Vector element count mismatch!");
2836  if (Operand.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF)
2837  return getUNDEF(VT);
2838  break;
2839  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2840  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
2841  "Invalid SIGN_EXTEND!");
2842  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
2843  assert(Operand.getValueType().getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
2844  "Invalid sext node, dst < src!");
2845  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
2846  VT.getVectorNumElements() ==
2847  Operand.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2848  "Vector element count mismatch!");
2849  if (OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
2850  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2851  else if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2852  // sext(undef) = 0, because the top bits will all be the same.
2853  return getConstant(0, VT);
2854  break;
2855  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2856  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
2857  "Invalid ZERO_EXTEND!");
2858  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
2859  assert(Operand.getValueType().getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
2860  "Invalid zext node, dst < src!");
2861  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
2862  VT.getVectorNumElements() ==
2863  Operand.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2864  "Vector element count mismatch!");
2865  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) // (zext (zext x)) -> (zext x)
2866  return getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, VT,
2867  Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2868  else if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2869  // zext(undef) = 0, because the top bits will be zero.
2870  return getConstant(0, VT);
2871  break;
2872  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
2873  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
2874  "Invalid ANY_EXTEND!");
2875  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop extension
2876  assert(Operand.getValueType().getScalarType().bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
2877  "Invalid anyext node, dst < src!");
2878  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
2879  VT.getVectorNumElements() ==
2880  Operand.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2881  "Vector element count mismatch!");
2882 
2883  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
2884  OpOpcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
2885  // (ext (zext x)) -> (zext x) and (ext (sext x)) -> (sext x)
2886  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2887  else if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2888  return getUNDEF(VT);
2889 
2890  // (ext (trunx x)) -> x
2891  if (OpOpcode == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
2892  SDValue OpOp = Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0);
2893  if (OpOp.getValueType() == VT)
2894  return OpOp;
2895  }
2896  break;
2897  case ISD::TRUNCATE:
2898  assert(VT.isInteger() && Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
2899  "Invalid TRUNCATE!");
2900  if (Operand.getValueType() == VT) return Operand; // noop truncate
2901  assert(Operand.getValueType().getScalarType().bitsGT(VT.getScalarType()) &&
2902  "Invalid truncate node, src < dst!");
2903  assert((!VT.isVector() ||
2904  VT.getVectorNumElements() ==
2905  Operand.getValueType().getVectorNumElements()) &&
2906  "Vector element count mismatch!");
2907  if (OpOpcode == ISD::TRUNCATE)
2908  return getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2909  if (OpOpcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || OpOpcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
2910  OpOpcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
2911  // If the source is smaller than the dest, we still need an extend.
2912  if (Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0).getValueType().getScalarType()
2913  .bitsLT(VT.getScalarType()))
2914  return getNode(OpOpcode, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2915  if (Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0).getValueType().bitsGT(VT))
2916  return getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2917  return Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0);
2918  }
2919  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2920  return getUNDEF(VT);
2921  break;
2922  case ISD::BITCAST:
2923  // Basic sanity checking.
2924  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() == Operand.getValueType().getSizeInBits()
2925  && "Cannot BITCAST between types of different sizes!");
2926  if (VT == Operand.getValueType()) return Operand; // noop conversion.
2927  if (OpOpcode == ISD::BITCAST) // bitconv(bitconv(x)) -> bitconv(x)
2928  return getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Operand.getOperand(0));
2929  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2930  return getUNDEF(VT);
2931  break;
2932  case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:
2933  assert(VT.isVector() && !Operand.getValueType().isVector() &&
2934  (VT.getVectorElementType() == Operand.getValueType() ||
2935  (VT.getVectorElementType().isInteger() &&
2936  Operand.getValueType().isInteger() &&
2937  VT.getVectorElementType().bitsLE(Operand.getValueType()))) &&
2938  "Illegal SCALAR_TO_VECTOR node!");
2939  if (OpOpcode == ISD::UNDEF)
2940  return getUNDEF(VT);
2941  // scalar_to_vector(extract_vector_elt V, 0) -> V, top bits are undefined.
2942  if (OpOpcode == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
2943  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Operand.getOperand(1)) &&
2944  Operand.getConstantOperandVal(1) == 0 &&
2945  Operand.getOperand(0).getValueType() == VT)
2946  return Operand.getOperand(0);
2947  break;
2948  case ISD::FNEG:
2949  // -(X-Y) -> (Y-X) is unsafe because when X==Y, -0.0 != +0.0
2950  if (getTarget().Options.UnsafeFPMath && OpOpcode == ISD::FSUB)
2951  return getNode(ISD::FSUB, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(1),
2952  Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2953  if (OpOpcode == ISD::FNEG) // --X -> X
2954  return Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0);
2955  break;
2956  case ISD::FABS:
2957  if (OpOpcode == ISD::FNEG) // abs(-X) -> abs(X)
2958  return getNode(ISD::FABS, DL, VT, Operand.getNode()->getOperand(0));
2959  break;
2960  }
2961 
2962  SDNode *N;
2963  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
2964  if (VT != MVT::Glue) { // Don't CSE flag producing nodes
2965  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2966  SDValue Ops[1] = { Operand };
2967  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
2968  void *IP = nullptr;
2969  if (SDNode *E = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, IP))
2970  return SDValue(E, 0);
2971 
2972  N = new (NodeAllocator) UnarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
2973  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs, Operand);
2974  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
2975  } else {
2976  N = new (NodeAllocator) UnarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
2977  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTs, Operand);
2978  }
2979 
2980  AllNodes.push_back(N);
2981 #ifndef NDEBUG
2982  VerifySDNode(N);
2983 #endif
2984  return SDValue(N, 0);
2985 }

3169  case ISD::MULHS:
3170  case ISD::MUL:
3171  case ISD::SDIV:
3172  case ISD::SREM:
3173  assert(VT.isInteger() && "This operator does not apply to FP types!");
3174  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
3175  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
3176  break;
3177  case ISD::FADD:
3178  case ISD::FSUB:
3179  case ISD::FMUL:
3180  case ISD::FDIV:
3181  case ISD::FREM:
3182  if (getTarget().Options.UnsafeFPMath) {
3183  if (Opcode == ISD::FADD) {
3184  // 0+x --> x
3185  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1))
3186  if (CFP->getValueAPF().isZero())
3187  return N2;
3188  // x+0 --> x
3189  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2))
3190  if (CFP->getValueAPF().isZero())
3191  return N1;
3192  } else if (Opcode == ISD::FSUB) {
3193  // x-0 --> x
3194  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2))
3195  if (CFP->getValueAPF().isZero())
3196  return N1;
3197  } else if (Opcode == ISD::FMUL) {
3198  ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1);
3199  SDValue V = N2;
3200 
3201  // If the first operand isn't the constant, try the second
3202  if (!CFP) {
3203  CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2);
3204  V = N1;
3205  }
3206 
3207  if (CFP) {
3208  // 0*x --> 0
3209  if (CFP->isZero())
3210  return SDValue(CFP,0);
3211  // 1*x --> x
3212  if (CFP->isExactlyValue(1.0))
3213  return V;
3214  }
3215  }
3216  }
3217  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "This operator only applies to FP types!");
3218  assert(N1.getValueType() == N2.getValueType() &&
3219  N1.getValueType() == VT && "Binary operator types must match!");
3220  break;
3221  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN: // N1 and result must match. N1/N2 need not match.
3222  assert(N1.getValueType() == VT &&
3223  N1.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
3224  N2.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
3225  "Invalid FCOPYSIGN!");
3226  break;
3227  case ISD::SHL:
3228  case ISD::SRA:
3229  case ISD::SRL:
3230  case ISD::ROTL:
3231  case ISD::ROTR:
3232  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() &&
3233  "Shift operators return type must be the same as their first arg");
3234  assert(VT.isInteger() && N2.getValueType().isInteger() &&
3235  "Shifts only work on integers");
3236  assert((!VT.isVector() || VT == N2.getValueType()) &&
3237  "Vector shift amounts must be in the same as their first arg");
3238  // Verify that the shift amount VT is bit enough to hold valid shift
3239  // amounts. This catches things like trying to shift an i1024 value by an
3240  // i8, which is easy to fall into in generic code that uses
3241  // TLI.getShiftAmount().
3242  assert(N2.getValueType().getSizeInBits() >=
3243  Log2_32_Ceil(N1.getValueType().getSizeInBits()) &&
3244  "Invalid use of small shift amount with oversized value!");
3245 
3246  // Always fold shifts of i1 values so the code generator doesn't need to
3247  // handle them. Since we know the size of the shift has to be less than the
3248  // size of the value, the shift/rotate count is guaranteed to be zero.
3249  if (VT == MVT::i1)
3250  return N1;
3251  if (N2C && N2C->isNullValue())
3252  return N1;
3253  break;
3254  case ISD::FP_ROUND_INREG: {
3255  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT();
3256  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && "Not an inreg round!");
3257  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && EVT.isFloatingPoint() &&
3258  "Cannot FP_ROUND_INREG integer types");
3259  assert(EVT.isVector() == VT.isVector() &&
3260  "FP_ROUND_INREG type should be vector iff the operand "
3261  "type is vector!");
3262  assert((!EVT.isVector() ||
3263  EVT.getVectorNumElements() == VT.getVectorNumElements()) &&
3264  "Vector element counts must match in FP_ROUND_INREG");
3265  assert(EVT.bitsLE(VT) && "Not rounding down!");
3266  (void)EVT;
3267  if (cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT() == VT) return N1; // Not actually rounding.
3268  break;
3269  }
3270  case ISD::FP_ROUND:
3271  assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() &&
3272  N1.getValueType().isFloatingPoint() &&
3273  VT.bitsLE(N1.getValueType()) &&
3274  isa<ConstantSDNode>(N2) && "Invalid FP_ROUND!");
3275  if (N1.getValueType() == VT) return N1; // noop conversion.
3276  break;
3277  case ISD::AssertSext:
3278  case ISD::AssertZext: {
3279  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT();
3280  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && "Not an inreg extend!");
3281  assert(VT.isInteger() && EVT.isInteger() &&
3282  "Cannot *_EXTEND_INREG FP types");
3283  assert(!EVT.isVector() &&
3284  "AssertSExt/AssertZExt type should be the vector element type "
3285  "rather than the vector type!");
3286  assert(EVT.bitsLE(VT) && "Not extending!");
3287  if (VT == EVT) return N1; // noop assertion.
3288  break;
3289  }
3290  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
3291  EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N2)->getVT();
3292  assert(VT == N1.getValueType() && "Not an inreg extend!");
3293  assert(VT.isInteger() && EVT.isInteger() &&
3294  "Cannot *_EXTEND_INREG FP types");
3295  assert(EVT.isVector() == VT.isVector() &&
3296  "SIGN_EXTEND_INREG type should be vector iff the operand "
3297  "type is vector!");
3298  assert((!EVT.isVector() ||
3299  EVT.getVectorNumElements() == VT.getVectorNumElements()) &&
3300  "Vector element counts must match in SIGN_EXTEND_INREG");
3301  assert(EVT.bitsLE(VT) && "Not extending!");
3302  if (EVT == VT) return N1; // Not actually extending
3303 
3304  if (N1C) {
3305  APInt Val = N1C->getAPIntValue();
3306  unsigned FromBits = EVT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits();
3307  Val <<= Val.getBitWidth()-FromBits;
3308  Val = Val.ashr(Val.getBitWidth()-FromBits);
3309  return getConstant(Val, VT);
3310  }
3311  break;
3312  }
3313  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
3314  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of an UNDEF is an UNDEF.
3315  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF)
3316  return getUNDEF(VT);
3317 
3318  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of CONCAT_VECTORS is often formed while lowering is
3319  // expanding copies of large vectors from registers.
3320  if (N2C &&
3321  N1.getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS &&
3322  N1.getNumOperands() > 0) {
3323  unsigned Factor =
3324  N1.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
3325  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT,
3326  N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue() / Factor),
3327  getConstant(N2C->getZExtValue() % Factor,
3328  N2.getValueType()));
3329  }
3330 
3331  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of BUILD_VECTOR is often formed while lowering is
3332  // expanding large vector constants.
3333  if (N2C && N1.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR) {
3334  SDValue Elt = N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue());
3335 
3336  if (VT != Elt.getValueType())
3337  // If the vector element type is not legal, the BUILD_VECTOR operands
3338  // are promoted and implicitly truncated, and the result implicitly
3339  // extended. Make that explicit here.
3340  Elt = getAnyExtOrTrunc(Elt, DL, VT);
3341 
3342  return Elt;
3343  }
3344 
3345  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT of INSERT_VECTOR_ELT is often formed when vector
3346  // operations are lowered to scalars.
3347  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT) {
3348  // If the indices are the same, return the inserted element else
3349  // if the indices are known different, extract the element from
3350  // the original vector.
3351  SDValue N1Op2 = N1.getOperand(2);
3352  ConstantSDNode *N1Op2C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1Op2.getNode());
3353 
3354  if (N1Op2C && N2C) {
3355  if (N1Op2C->getZExtValue() == N2C->getZExtValue()) {
3356  if (VT == N1.getOperand(1).getValueType())
3357  return N1.getOperand(1);
3358  else
3359  return getSExtOrTrunc(N1.getOperand(1), DL, VT);
3360  }
3361 
3362  return getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, VT, N1.getOperand(0), N2);
3363  }
3364  }
3365  break;
3366  case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT:
3367  assert(N2C && (unsigned)N2C->getZExtValue() < 2 && "Bad EXTRACT_ELEMENT!");
3368  assert(!N1.getValueType().isVector() && !VT.isVector() &&
3369  (N1.getValueType().isInteger() == VT.isInteger()) &&
3370  N1.getValueType() != VT &&
3371  "Wrong types for EXTRACT_ELEMENT!");
3372 
3373  // EXTRACT_ELEMENT of BUILD_PAIR is often formed while legalize is expanding
3374  // 64-bit integers into 32-bit parts. Instead of building the extract of
3375  // the BUILD_PAIR, only to have legalize rip it apart, just do it now.
3376  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_PAIR)
3377  return N1.getOperand(N2C->getZExtValue());
3378 
3379  // EXTRACT_ELEMENT of a constant int is also very common.
3380  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)) {
3381  unsigned ElementSize = VT.getSizeInBits();
3382  unsigned Shift = ElementSize * N2C->getZExtValue();
3383  APInt ShiftedVal = C->getAPIntValue().lshr(Shift);
3384  return getConstant(ShiftedVal.trunc(ElementSize), VT);
3385  }
3386  break;
3387  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
3388  SDValue Index = N2;
3389  if (VT.isSimple() && N1.getValueType().isSimple()) {
3390  assert(VT.isVector() && N1.getValueType().isVector() &&
3391  "Extract subvector VTs must be a vectors!");
3392  assert(VT.getVectorElementType() ==
3393  N1.getValueType().getVectorElementType() &&
3394  "Extract subvector VTs must have the same element type!");
3395  assert(VT.getSimpleVT() <= N1.getSimpleValueType() &&
3396  "Extract subvector must be from larger vector to smaller vector!");
3397 
3398  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Index.getNode())) {
3399  assert((VT.getVectorNumElements() +
3400  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Index.getNode())->getZExtValue()
3401  <= N1.getValueType().getVectorNumElements())
3402  && "Extract subvector overflow!");
3403  }
3404 
3405  // Trivial extraction.
3406  if (VT.getSimpleVT() == N1.getSimpleValueType())
3407  return N1;
3408  }
3409  break;
3410  }
3411  }
3412 
3413  // Perform trivial constant folding.
3414  SDValue SV = FoldConstantArithmetic(Opcode, VT, N1.getNode(), N2.getNode());
3415  if (SV.getNode()) return SV;
3416 
3417  // Canonicalize constant to RHS if commutative.
3418  if (N1C && !N2C && isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode)) {
3419  std::swap(N1C, N2C);
3420  std::swap(N1, N2);
3421  }
3422 
3423  // Constant fold FP operations.
3424  ConstantFPSDNode *N1CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N1.getNode());
3425  ConstantFPSDNode *N2CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N2.getNode());
3426  if (N1CFP) {
3427  if (!N2CFP && isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode)) {
3428  // Canonicalize constant to RHS if commutative.
3429  std::swap(N1CFP, N2CFP);
3430  std::swap(N1, N2);
3431  } else if (N2CFP) {
3432  APFloat V1 = N1CFP->getValueAPF(), V2 = N2CFP->getValueAPF();
3433  APFloat::opStatus s;
3434  switch (Opcode) {
3435  case ISD::FADD:
3436  s = V1.add(V2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3437  if (s != APFloat::opInvalidOp)
3438  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3439  break;
3440  case ISD::FSUB:
3441  s = V1.subtract(V2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3442  if (s!=APFloat::opInvalidOp)
3443  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3444  break;
3445  case ISD::FMUL:
3446  s = V1.multiply(V2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3447  if (s!=APFloat::opInvalidOp)
3448  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3449  break;
3450  case ISD::FDIV:
3451  s = V1.divide(V2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3452  if (s!=APFloat::opInvalidOp && s!=APFloat::opDivByZero)
3453  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3454  break;
3455  case ISD::FREM :
3456  s = V1.mod(V2, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3457  if (s!=APFloat::opInvalidOp && s!=APFloat::opDivByZero)
3458  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3459  break;
3460  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:
3461  V1.copySign(V2);
3462  return getConstantFP(V1, VT);
3463  default: break;
3464  }
3465  }
3466 
3467  if (Opcode == ISD::FP_ROUND) {
3468  APFloat V = N1CFP->getValueAPF(); // make copy
3469  bool ignored;
3470  // This can return overflow, underflow, or inexact; we don't care.
3471  // FIXME need to be more flexible about rounding mode.
3472  (void)V.convert(EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT),
3473  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored);
3474  return getConstantFP(V, VT);
3475  }
3476  }
3477 
3478  // Canonicalize an UNDEF to the RHS, even over a constant.
3479  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF) {
3480  if (isCommutativeBinOp(Opcode)) {
3481  std::swap(N1, N2);
3482  } else {
3483  switch (Opcode) {
3484  case ISD::FP_ROUND_INREG:
3485  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
3486  case ISD::SUB:
3487  case ISD::FSUB:
3488  case ISD::FDIV:
3489  case ISD::FREM:
3490  case ISD::SRA:
3491  return N1; // fold op(undef, arg2) -> undef
3492  case ISD::UDIV:
3493  case ISD::SDIV:
3494  case ISD::UREM:
3495  case ISD::SREM:
3496  case ISD::SRL:
3497  case ISD::SHL:
3498  if (!VT.isVector())
3499  return getConstant(0, VT); // fold op(undef, arg2) -> 0
3500  // For vectors, we can't easily build an all zero vector, just return
3501  // the LHS.
3502  return N2;
3503  }
3504  }
3505  }
3506 
3507  // Fold a bunch of operators when the RHS is undef.
3508  if (N2.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF) {
3509  switch (Opcode) {
3510  case ISD::XOR:
3511  if (N1.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF)
3512  // Handle undef ^ undef -> 0 special case. This is a common
3513  // idiom (misuse).
3514  return getConstant(0, VT);
3515  // fallthrough
3516  case ISD::ADD:
3517  case ISD::ADDC:
3518  case ISD::ADDE:
3519  case ISD::SUB:
3520  case ISD::UDIV:
3521  case ISD::SDIV:
3522  case ISD::UREM:
3523  case ISD::SREM:
3524  return N2; // fold op(arg1, undef) -> undef
3525  case ISD::FADD:
3526  case ISD::FSUB:
3527  case ISD::FMUL:
3528  case ISD::FDIV:
3529  case ISD::FREM:
3530  if (getTarget().Options.UnsafeFPMath)
3531  return N2;
3532  break;
3533  case ISD::MUL:
3534  case ISD::AND:
3535  case ISD::SRL:
3536  case ISD::SHL:
3537  if (!VT.isVector())
3538  return getConstant(0, VT); // fold op(arg1, undef) -> 0
3539  // For vectors, we can't easily build an all zero vector, just return
3540  // the LHS.
3541  return N1;
3542  case ISD::OR:
3543  if (!VT.isVector())
3544  return getConstant(APInt::getAllOnesValue(VT.getSizeInBits()), VT);
3545  // For vectors, we can't easily build an all one vector, just return
3546  // the LHS.
3547  return N1;
3548  case ISD::SRA:
3549  return N1;
3550  }
3551  }
3552 
3553  // Memoize this node if possible.
3554  BinarySDNode *N;
3555  SDVTList VTs = getVTList(VT);
3556  const bool BinOpHasFlags = isBinOpWithFlags(Opcode);
3557  if (VT != MVT::Glue) {
3558  SDValue Ops[] = {N1, N2};
3559  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3560  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTs, Ops);
3561  if (BinOpHasFlags)
3562  AddBinaryNodeIDCustom(ID, Opcode, nuw, nsw, exact);
3563  void *IP = nullptr;
3564  if (SDNode *E = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, IP))
3565  return SDValue(E, 0);
3566 
3567  N = GetBinarySDNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, N1, N2, nuw, nsw, exact);
3568 
3569  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
3570  } else {
3571 
3572  N = GetBinarySDNode(Opcode, DL, VTs, N1, N2, nuw, nsw, exact);
3573  }
3574 
3575  AllNodes.push_back(N);
3576 #ifndef NDEBUG
3577  VerifySDNode(N);
3578 #endif
3579  return SDValue(N, 0);
3580 }

5068  else if (N3.getOpcode() == ISD::AND)
5069  if (ConstantSDNode *AndRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N3.getOperand(1))) {
5070  // If the and is only masking out bits that cannot effect the shift,
5071  // eliminate the and.
5072  unsigned NumBits = VT.getScalarType().getSizeInBits()*2;
5073  if ((AndRHS->getValue() & (NumBits-1)) == NumBits-1)
5074  return getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, N1, N2, N3.getOperand(0));
5075  }
5076  break;
5077  }
5078 #endif
5079 
5080  // Memoize the node unless it returns a flag.
5081  SDNode *N;
5082  unsigned NumOps = Ops.size();
5083  if (VTList.VTs[VTList.NumVTs-1] != MVT::Glue) {
5084  FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5085  AddNodeIDNode(ID, Opcode, VTList, Ops);
5086  void *IP = nullptr;
5087  if (SDNode *E = CSEMap.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, IP))
5088  return SDValue(E, 0);
5089 
5090  if (NumOps == 1) {
5091  N = new (NodeAllocator) UnarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5092  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0]);
5093  } else if (NumOps == 2) {
5094  N = new (NodeAllocator) BinarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5095  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0],
5096  Ops[1]);
5097  } else if (NumOps == 3) {
5098  N = new (NodeAllocator) TernarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5099  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0],
5100  Ops[1], Ops[2]);
5101  } else {
5102  N = new (NodeAllocator) SDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(),
5103  VTList, Ops);
5104  }
5105  CSEMap.InsertNode(N, IP);
5106  } else {
5107  if (NumOps == 1) {
5108  N = new (NodeAllocator) UnarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5109  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0]);
5110  } else if (NumOps == 2) {
5111  N = new (NodeAllocator) BinarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5112  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0],
5113  Ops[1]);
5114  } else if (NumOps == 3) {
5115  N = new (NodeAllocator) TernarySDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(),
5116  DL.getDebugLoc(), VTList, Ops[0],
5117  Ops[1], Ops[2]);
5118  } else {
5119  N = new (NodeAllocator) SDNode(Opcode, DL.getIROrder(), DL.getDebugLoc(),
5120  VTList, Ops);
5121  }
5122  }
5123  AllNodes.push_back(N);
5124 #ifndef NDEBUG
5125  VerifySDNode(N);
5126 #endif
5127  return SDValue(N, 0);
5128 }

getVectorShuffle - Return an ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE node. The number of elements in VT, which must be a vector type, must match the number of mask elements NumElts. A integer mask element equal to -1 is treated as undefined.

bool SelectionDAG::LegalizeVectors ( )

LegalizeVectors - This transforms the SelectionDAG into a SelectionDAG that only uses vector math operations supported by the target. This is necessary as a separate step from Legalize because unrolling a vector operation can introduce illegal types, which requires running LegalizeTypes again.

Note that this is an involved process that may invalidate pointers into the graph.

SDNode * SelectionDAG::MorphNodeTo ( SDNode *  N,
unsigned  Opc,
SDVTList  VTs,
ArrayRef< SDValue >  Ops 
)

MorphNodeTo - This mutates the specified node to have the specified return type, opcode, and operands.

MorphNodeTo - This mutates the specified node to have the specified return type, opcode, and operands.

Note that MorphNodeTo returns the resultant node. If there is already a node of the specified opcode and operands, it returns that node instead of the current one. Note that the SDLoc need not be the same.

Using MorphNodeTo is faster than creating a new node and swapping it in with ReplaceAllUsesWith both because it often avoids allocating a new node, and because it doesn't require CSE recalculation for any of the node's users.

RemoveNodeFromCSEMaps - Take the specified node out of the CSE map that correspond to it. This is useful when we're about to delete or repurpose the node. We don't want future request for structurally identical nodes to return N anymore.

void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith ( const SDValue *  From,

)

ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith - Like ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith, but for multiple values at once. This correctly handles the case where there is an overlap between the From values and the To values.

ReplaceAllUsesOfValuesWith - Replace any uses of From with To, leaving uses of other values produced by From.getNode() alone. The same value may appear in both the From and To list. The Deleted vector is handled the same way as for ReplaceAllUsesWith.

void SelectionDAG::ReplaceAllUsesWith ( SDValue  FromN,
SDValue  To 
)

ReplaceAllUsesWith - Modify anything using 'From' to use 'To' instead. This can cause recursive merging of nodes in the DAG. Use the first version if 'From' is known to have a single result, use the second if you have two nodes with identical results (or if 'To' has a superset of the results of 'From'), use the third otherwise.

These methods all take an optional UpdateListener, which (if not null) is informed about nodes that are deleted and modified due to recursive changes in the dag.

These functions only replace all existing uses. It's possible that as these replacements are being performed, CSE may cause the From node to be given new uses. These new uses of From are left in place, and not automatically transferred to To.

ReplaceAllUsesWith - Modify anything using 'From' to use 'To' instead. This can cause recursive merging of nodes in the DAG.

This version assumes From has a single result value.

SDValue SelectionDAG::UnrollVectorOp ( SDNode *  N,
unsigned  ResNE = 0 
)

UnrollVectorOp - Utility function used by legalize and lowering to "unroll" a vector operation by splitting out the scalars and operating on each element individually. If the ResNE is 0, fully unroll the vector op. If ResNE is less than the width of the vector op, unroll up to ResNE. If the ResNE is greater than the width of the vector op, unroll the vector op and fill the end of the resulting vector with UNDEFS.

UpdadeSDLocOnMergedSDNode - If the opt level is -O0 then it throws away the line number information on the merged node since it is not possible to preserve the information that operation is associated with multiple lines. This will make the debugger working better at -O0, were there is a higher probability having other instructions associated with that line.

SDNode * SelectionDAG::UpdateNodeOperands ( SDNode *  N,
SDValue  Op 
)

UpdateNodeOperands - Mutate the specified node in-place to have the specified operands. If the resultant node already exists in the DAG, this does not modify the specified node, instead it returns the node that already exists. If the resultant node does not exist in the DAG, the input node is returned. As a degenerate case, if you specify the same input operands as the node already has, the input node is returned.

bool llvm::SelectionDAG::NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes

NewNodesMustHaveLegalTypes - When true, additional steps are taken to ensure that getConstant() and similar functions return DAG nodes that have legal types. This is important after type legalization since any illegally typed nodes generated after this point will not experience type legalization.
